{"name":"Steal Thoughts","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You take mental damage or attempt a saving throw against a mental effect.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You steal a portion of your assailant’s thoughts. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened} condition until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>You can use the extra action to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.QNAVeNKtHA0EUw4X]{Feint}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.2u915NdUyQan6uKF]{Demoralize}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.BlAOM2X92SI6HMtJ]{Seek}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1xRFPTFtWtGJ9ELw]{Sense Motive}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"steal-thoughts","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978089954,"modifiedTime":1685981244777,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"2joKYzF0Rj8AqjYK"}
{"name":"Mesmerist Dedication","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You cast spells like a mesmerist and gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} activity. You gain a Focus Pool with 1 Focus Point.</p>\n<p>You gain one manipulation spell of your choice, and one common Cue, Stare, or Treatment of 1st level. You’re trained in spell attack rolls and spell DCs for occult spells. Your key spellcasting ability for mesmerist archetype spells is Charisma, and they are occult mesmerist spells. You become trained in Occultism, or another skill if you were already trained.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained two other feats from the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-magic-journals.6DPJqrJJBdYR5hbz.JournalEntryPage.rvHrzWTwH8afSVsC]{Mesmerist} archetype.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.custom.modifiers.mesmerist-dedication-count","value":1},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.skills.occ.rank","value":1},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.proficiencies.traditions.occult.rank","value":1}],"slug":"mesmerist-dedication","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["archetype","dedication","multiclass"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Charisma 14"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685983173458,"modifiedTime":1685984856848,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"2mqEUkkPs2X20VSJ"}
{"name":"Umbral Summons","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>When you cast a summon spell, designate a single target.</p>\n<p>The creature you summon is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.DmAIPqOBomZ7H95W]{Concealed} to the target.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"umbral-summons","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685869762125,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"3CJMz2kj36fNvcIX"}
{"name":"Basic Hypnotism","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You use your knack skill to manipulate others’ minds.</p>\n<p>You can use your knack skill instead of Deception to Feint, instead of Diplomacy to Make an Impression, and instead of Intimidation to Demoralize. You can use your proficiency rank in your knack skill to meet the requirements of skill feats that require a particular rank in Deception, Diplomacy, or Intimidation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"basic-hypnotism","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"a knack skill"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685860734011,"modifiedTime":1685867704291,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"3RZT0CJBv0AtD1kL"}
