{"name":"Manipulator","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You program others’ minds with instructions as though winding a clock.</p>\n<p><strong>Cue</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.59NVyxDi2uglDR7i]{Programmed Reaction}</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong>: Diplomacy</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.skills.dip.rank","value":1}],"slug":"manipulator","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-06-03T09:36:00.290+04:00","version":{"schema":0.84,"foundry":"10.291","system":"4.12.7"}}},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685770436155,"modifiedTime":1685861848206,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"ja5BiknKmanKWe4M"}
{"name":"Program Mastery","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your mesmerism claws at the basic willpower within constructs. Constructs are not immune to your emotion and mental effects.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"program-mastery","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Program Manipulator"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978075448,"modifiedTime":1685980792993,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"ja7pahQhsxAHVuXc"}
{"name":"Potent Nightmares","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>When you use @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.b5pZUnTyORT2sUbb]{Dreadful Sleep}, you can choose to cast @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.new-spell-and-items-new-spells.DLUIuefHE36CWYX3]{Nightly Torment} instead of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Uqj344bezBq3ESdq]{Nightmare}. Either way, a target @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued} from your use of @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.b5pZUnTyORT2sUbb]{Dreadful Sleep} can’t recover from the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued} condition until they have two full nights’ rest on consecutive nights. They are also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 2} while @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued}in this way.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"potent-nightmares","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":14},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Dreadful Sleep"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685983258531,"modifiedTime":1685983602766,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"jcn1k6sQWjaaKv2o"}
{"name":"Unassailable Mind","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You gain the stupefied condition when you weren’t stupefied previously.</p>\n<p><strong>Grants</strong> @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-effects.ULpbYCgrJgYIzWmR]{Effect: Unassailable Mind}</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Choose Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma. You don’t apply the status penalty from the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied} condition to checks and DCs based on this ability.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"unassailable-mind","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978104404,"modifiedTime":1685982358640,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"jw4Qegp1x8w1qSkX"}
{"name":"Star Reader","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You see an ally fail a check.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You grant your ally a +1 circumstance bonus to the check, possibly changing the outcome.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"star-reader","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Chart Caster"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978089954,"modifiedTime":1685981244776,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"lOyDKIV5Rnz8eIf6"}
{"name":"Alter Ego","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You spend your off hours spreading stories and planting evidence of a nonexistent alter ego. As long as you spend at least 8 hours engaging in this activity each week in a settlement, you can attempt a Deception check at the end of the week to determine how firmly this settlement believes in the existence of this alter ego. The DC is a standard DC for the settlement’s level, possibly adjusted within GM discretion based on the magnitude and credibility of the disinformation you disseminate.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Most of the residents are aware of your alter ego and believe in their existence. For the next week, when you attempt socially oriented actions (such as @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.tHCqgwjtQtzNqVvd]{Coerce}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.QyzlsLrqM0EEwd7j]{Earn Income}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.ewwCglB7XOPLUz72]{Lie}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.OX4fy22hQgUHDr0q]{Make an Impression}) against members of this settlement, you can invoke information about your alter ego to gain a +2 circumstance bonus on the required check. Additionally, subject to GM discretion, for the next week you can claim a connection with your alter ego to gain entrance to exclusive events, arrange a meeting with notable residents, gain access to uncommon or rare items, or accomplish other social tasks that would normally lie beyond your reach within the settlement. Each time you claim this connection, you fall under greater public scrutiny, and the DC for this activity increases by 2.</p>\n<p><strong>Success </strong>As critical success, but the circumstance bonus is only +1 and the DC increases by 5 after you claim a connection with your alter ego.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure </strong>Some residents might be aware of the name of your alter ego but not to a degree that offers you any benefits. You may continue to use this activity without any hindrance.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> You spread contradictory or unbelievable information. The DC for this activity increases by 2.</p>\n<p>At any time, you can discontinue spreading information about your alter ego and begin developing a new alter ego. Doing so resets the DC for this activity.</p>\n<p>You can maintain only one alter ego at a time, and you usually can’t renew an alter ego that you discontinued or that was exposed as false (subject to GM discretion).</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"alter-ego","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["downtime","hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"trained in Deception"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685978291370,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"lrDEc4nw9kC4ZAGY"}
{"name":"Sonomancer","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You specialize in manipulating the minds of the sleeping.</p>\n<p>When you roll a critical failure against a sleep effect, you get a failure, instead. When a target rolls a success against your sleep effect, they get a failure, instead. Add @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.o4lRVTwSxnOOn5vl]{Sleep} to your spell repertoire and signature spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"adjustment":{"criticalFailure":"one-degree-better"},"key":"AdjustDegreeOfSuccess","selector":"saving-throw","type":"save","predicate":["sleep"]}],"slug":"sonomancer","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685869762120,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"lu0LdVpN2iNsyORe"}
{"name":"Basic Mesmerism","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level mesmerist feat.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"adjustName":false,"allowedDrops":{"label":"PF2E.SpecificRule.Prompt.LevelOneOrTwoClassFeat","predicate":["item:type:feat","item:trait:hb_mesmerist"]},"choices":{"query":"{\"system.level.value\":{\"$lte\":2},\"system.traits.value\":{\"$elemMatch\":\"hb_mesmerist\"}}"},"flag":"basicMesmerism","key":"ChoiceSet","prompt":"PF2E.SpecificRule.Prompt.LevelOneOrTwoClassFeat"},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.custom.modifiers.mesmerist-dedication-count","value":1},{"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"{item|flags.pf2e.rulesSelections.basicMesmerism}"}],"slug":"basic-mesmerism","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Mesmerist Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685983173458,"modifiedTime":1685985350842,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"nGCc7e0P4IsVCZOt"}
{"name":"Networked Knowledge","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You gain two pieces of information after @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recalling Knowledge} using a skill in which you are master.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your mind palace is well organized and allows you to quickly recall related information. Attempt to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge} again, using a different skill than the one you used in the triggering check. If your triggering check was a failure or critical failure, this check automatically fails. If you’re untrained in the second skill, add your level as a proficiency bonus.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"networked-knowledge","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Mind Palace"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685860734011,"modifiedTime":1685862176614,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"q9HNlWYkinF0XwlZ"}
{"name":"Chart Caster","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You keep a book of occult spells, similar to a wizard’s spellbook, and can use its spells to supplement your spell repertoire. Add all the spells in your repertoire to this book for free. You can use the Occultism skill to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spells} and add them to your spellbook by paying the appropriate cost, similar to a wizard.</p>\n<p>During your daily preparations, choose any one spell from your book of occult spells. If that spell is already in your spell repertoire, you can treat it as an additional signature spell that day. If it isn’t in your repertoire, treat it as though it were until your next daily preparations.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"chart-caster","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"a spell repertoire"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685869762101,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qNxnjhxl236B6vNe"}
{"name":"Size Up","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You roll initiative.</p>\n<p><strong>Target </strong>one other creature rolling initiative </p>\n<hr />\n<p>Attempt to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge} about the target, without the secret trait. On a failure or critical failure, you learn nothing. If you succeed, in addition to the usual effects, you can choose to go immediately before or immediately after the target in initiative order instead of rolling initiative.</p>\n<p>If more than one character uses this ability or another ability to in the same place in initiative, use the normal rules for resolving a tie: NPCs and monsters act before PCs, and within those groups, the creatures can choose whichever order they want.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"size-up","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685869762113,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qPR7OJRBYUNL04MP"}
{"name":"Practiced Hypnotist","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You gain one additional 3rd-level spell slot, 4th-level spell slot, and 5th-level spell slot. You can use these spell slots only to cast @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.K2WpC3FFoHrqX9Q5]{Hypnotic Pattern}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.qwlh6aDgi86U3Q7H]{Suggestion}, and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.GP3wewkQXEPrLxYj]{Subconscious Suggestion}, respectively. If you have a spell repertoire and these spells weren’t already in your spell repertoire, you add them to your spell repertoire.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"practiced-hypnotist","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978104404,"modifiedTime":1685982237229,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qbcAs1BwuUk5HA1d"}
{"name":"Axis","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Granted Spells</strong>: 1st @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.aEM2cttJ2eYcLssW]{Fleet Step}, 2nd @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.MVrxZarUTnJxAUN8]{Tether}, 4th @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.McnPlLFvKtQVXNcG]{Shape Stone}, 6th @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.2BV2yYPfVJ5zirZt]{Stoneskin}</p>\n<p><strong>Stare</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.K67MELWEljGJcLDL]{Word Fumble}</p>\n<p><strong>Planar Essence</strong>: Select a target creature within 30 feet and choose @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.UHpkTuCtyaPqiCAB]{Step}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Stride}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.VjxZFuUXrCU94MWR]{Strike}. The next time the target attempts that action, they must succeed at a Will save against your occult spell DC or lose the action. Regardless of the outcome, the target is immune to this effect for 24 hours.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"axis","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685771107381,"modifiedTime":1685982880236,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qenB2iBxX2idh6Wb"}
{"name":"Planar Essence","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Reaching deep into your mind, you call forth a sample of material from another plane. The effect of this material is determined by your planar connection, as specified in its Planar Essence entry.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"planar-essence","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":12},"traits":{"value":["conjuration","hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":2},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685982397086,"modifiedTime":1685982937191,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qmUtLmJn59e69b1H"}
{"name":"Mesmerizing Specialty","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Choose an occult spell up to half your level rounded up with the enchantment or illusion trait. It must be a common spell or a spell you have access to. You can cast this spell once per day as an occult innate spell, heightened to half your level rounded up.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"mesmerizing-specialty","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867888379,"modifiedTime":1685869762127,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"tFQJFbd2i9gXf5Wo"}
{"name":"Widen Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You manipulate the energy of your spell, causing it to affect a wider area. If the next action you use is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} that has an area of a burst, cone, or line and does not have a duration, increase the area of that spell. Add 5 feet to the radius of a burst that normally has a radius of at least 10 feet (a burst with a smaller radius is not affected). Add 5 feet to the length of a cone or line that is normally 15 feet long or smaller, and add 10 feet to the length of a larger cone or line.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"widen-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["manipulate","hb_mesmerist","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685860734011,"modifiedTime":1685867704292,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"tX5VCWsHXBlXsqpr"}
{"name":"Mental Paragon","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You have tuned your spellcasting to the highest caliber. Add two common 10th-level occult spells to your repertoire. You gain a single 10th-level spell slot you can use to cast one of those two spells using mesmerist spellcasting. You don’t gain more 10th-level spells as you level up, unlike other spell slots, and you can’t use 10th-level slots with abilities that give you more spell slots or that let you cast spells without expending spell slots.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"mental-paragon","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":19},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685867057884,"modifiedTime":1685867084570,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"utpgIvaCiROcFZAr"}
{"name":"Basic Mesmerist Spellcasting","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You gain a spell repertoire. You gain the basic spellcasting benefits. Each time you gain a spell slot of a new level from the mesmerist archetype, add a common occult spell or another spell you learned or discovered to your repertoire, of the appropriate spell level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"basic-mesmerist-spellcasting","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Mesmerist Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685983173458,"modifiedTime":1685984926691,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"vFjMSjMQLVCrDjUf"}
{"name":"Hypnotherapist","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You use suggestion to alter others’ behavior.</p>\n<p><strong>Treatment</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.8SclME2GUGzwcwCL]{Mind of Stone}</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong>: Medicine</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.skills.med.rank","value":1}],"slug":"hypnotherapist","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-06-03T09:36:00.290+04:00","version":{"schema":0.84,"foundry":"10.291","system":"4.12.7"}}},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685770436155,"modifiedTime":1685861837319,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"w4gRMSwFUSBbRwt5"}
{"name":"Elysium, Heaven, or Nirvana","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Granted Spells</strong>: 1st @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal}, 3rd @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.DyiD239dNS7RIxZE]{Searing Light}, 4th @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.DZ9bzXYqMjAK9TzC]{Holy Cascade}, 5th @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Hnc7eGi7vyZenAIm]{Breath of Life}</p>\n<p><strong>Treatment</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.CJYfcCdCIusY1OwG]{Suppress Condition}</p>\n<p><strong>Planar Essence</strong>: You expend one of your spell slots to cast a 1-action @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal} spell at that spell level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"elysium-heaven-or-nirvana","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685771107381,"modifiedTime":1685978297542,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"w5untdq2QAyLV3OB"}
{"name":"Manipulation Spells","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>As a mesmerist, you learn three manipulation spells: implant cue, mesmerist stare, and touch treatment.<br />Manipulation spells are a type of focus spell. It costs 1 Focus Point to cast a focus spell, and you start with a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to study another creature’s mind, plumb the depths of your own mind, or psychically connect to your plane.</p>\n<p>Focus spells are automatically heightened to half your level rounded up, much like cantrips. Focus spells don't require spell slots, and you can’t cast them using spell slots. Taking feats can give you more focus spells and increase the size of your focus pool, though your focus pool can never hold more than 3 Focus Points.</p>\n<p>Your three manipulation spells use Cues (implant cue), Stares (mesmerist stare), and Touches (touch treatment). You learn one Cue, Stare, or Touch from your knack and one from your planar connection. You can learn others from mesmerist class feats. Your Cues, Stares, and Touches heighten to the same level as your manipulation spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.resources.focus.max","priority":10,"value":1}],"slug":"manipulation-spells","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685866171037,"modifiedTime":1685866335723,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"wIFlv3TiGATJvDNw"}
{"name":"Planar Passage","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.5bTt2CvYHPvaR7QQ]{Plane Shift} as an occult innate spell. You can cast it twice per week. This can be used only to travel back and forth between the Material Plane and the plane you selected for your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.Ec53YT5gJ06kRVLi]{Planar Connection}. (If your planar connection is with the Material Plane, you instead can travel from any plane to the Material Plane, and vice versa.) Due to your mind’s natural resonance with this plane, you can act as the spell focus, and you don’t require a tuning fork.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"planar-passage","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"a planar connection"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685860734011,"modifiedTime":1685983219293,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"xXph5Ms2XUaJUGfF"}
{"name":"Quick Cue","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You activate a Cue.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You cast implant cue, targeting the same creature as the triggering Cue. You must spend a Focus Point as usual.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"quick-cue","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"implant cue"},{"value":"a Cue"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978075448,"modifiedTime":1685980792994,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"xrdRBginuWRavWT5"}
{"name":"Efficient Treatment","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You cast @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.11hl5A2wGkUvaRmZ]{Touch Treatment} twice on the same target. You must spend 2 Focus Points as usual. When you heighten @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.11hl5A2wGkUvaRmZ]{Touch Treatment} to 6th level, you can use this activity to cast @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-spells.11hl5A2wGkUvaRmZ]{Touch Treatment} twice on the same two targets.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"efficient-treatment","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":3},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"touch treatment"},{"value":"a Treatment"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978075448,"modifiedTime":1685980792991,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"yahsqx86bQdGp8vr"}
{"name":"New Stare","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You learn a new Stare, of a level up to half your level rounded up. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can take this feat again. Each time, choose a new Stare.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1}],"slug":"new-stare","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":null,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"mesmerist stare"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685860734011,"modifiedTime":1685985623198,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"yvRAl73ObRgAjmLY"}
{"name":"Mesmerist Expansion","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You learn any combination of two new Cues, Stares, or Treatments. You must already know the associated spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can take this feat multiple times. Each time, select two more options.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[],"slug":"mesmerist-expansion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":null,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"implant cue, mesmerist stare, or touch treatment"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685978075448,"modifiedTime":1685985637912,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"z0zWukaPGdKVsWf9"}
{"name":"Mesmerist Weapon Expertise","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You have become thoroughly adept with mesmerist weapons. You gain expert proficiency in simple weapons and unarmed attacks. When you critically succeed at an attack roll using one of these weapons or an unarmed attack against a target currently affected by one of your spells, you apply the critical specialization effect for that weapon or unarmed attack.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Mind"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.martial.simple.rank","value":2},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.martial.unarmed.rank","value":2},{"domain":"all","key":"RollOption","label":"target currently affected by one of your spells","option":"mesmerist-critical-specialization","toggleable":true},{"key":"CriticalSpecialization","predicate":["mesmerist-critical-specialization",{"or":["item:category:simple","item:category:unarmed"]}]}],"slug":"mesmerist-weapon-expertise","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":11},"traits":{"value":["hb_mesmerist"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/classes/weapon-expertise.webp","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685866554471,"modifiedTime":1685866887050,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"z8Tkwlsvx0O21M5n"}
